# Coding Invariants (always-on)

These apply to every change. They are the lightweight, non-negotiable
subset — see the `quality-coding` skill for the full design guidance and
anti-pattern catalog.

## Never

- **No paid dependencies.** No Tavily/Exa/Cohere/OpenAI-API. SearxNG +
  Gemini free tier + GLM via z.ai only. If a feature needs paid, flag it
  and propose a free alternative. (See `zero-cost-constraint` rule.)
- **No keys/secrets in source.** API keys live in `config.json` in the
  `vane-data` volume. Never in `.ts`, `.env`, `Dockerfile`, or committed
  config.
- **No N+1 external calls.** Don't `await Promise.all(arr.map(async x =>
  await fetch(...)))` over a known set — batch into one call where the API
  supports arrays, or parallelize without per-item awaits.
- **No new LLM round-trip in speed mode.** Speed budget is ~3 calls
  (classify + 1 research iter + writer). Gate new LLM features to
  balanced/quality.
- **No `chat.completions.parse()` on GLM** — it strict-parses before
  fence-repair runs. Use `.create()` + `repairJson({ extractJson: true })`.

## Always

- **`try/catch` every external call** (SearxNG, scrape, LLM, embeddings)
  with a graceful fallback. The pipeline degrades, never hard-crashes.
- **Ship pipeline changes with a `docs/RESEARCH_PIPELINE.md` update** in
  the same change (algorithm catalog, flow, or tuning-knobs table).
- **Keep `modeModels.ts` / provider default model lists in sync** with
  what the API actually serves — verify with a curl when adding a model.
- **File-level header + JSDoc** on new pipeline-public modules/exports.
